    "According to Colla et al. [67], low value care refers to application of care that is unlikely to benefit the patient considering the cost, alternative options available, and patient preferences.",
    "To determine the appropriateness of a test, we emphasize the need for comprehensive Test ordering decision-making is a complex task that requires time and high-intensity attention.",
    "When interviewed, ICU physicians disclose that they do not have the necessary time to thoroughly assess the appropriate tests to order from the unnecessary ones [84].",
    "In this context, interventions to reduce inappropriateness can be perceived as an additional strain.",
    "On the contrary, well-executed interventions can influence physicians' test-ordering behavior [22]."
